parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electronic power steering can cause the steering wheel to become stiff or difficult to turn, making it hard to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The power steering fails to function
the steering wheel becomes stiff or difficult to turn
the vehicle is hard to maneuver
the power steering assist motor fails
the steering column fails
the power steering torque sensor fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column assembly can cause the steering wheel to become stiff or difficult to turn, making it hard to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes stiff or difficult to turn
the power steering fails to function
the steering column fails
the vehicle is hard to maneuver.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front K-frame (subframe) can cause the steering wheel to become stiff or difficult to turn, making it hard to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes stiff or difficult to turn
the vehicle is hard to maneuver
the lower control arm fractures due to severely rusted bolts.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or become unresponsive, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
the transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle jerks or bucks
the transmission overheats
the vehicle is unable to shift gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ETB can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or become unresponsive, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
the engine surges or hesitates
the vehicle jerks or bucks
the "wrench" light or throttle body/powertrain light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transfer case can cause the vehicle to lose power, overheat, or become unresponsive, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transfer case overheats
the vehicle loses power
the vehicle jerks or bucks
metal fragments are found in the transfer case fluid.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the wheel bearing can cause the vehicle to vibrate or shake, which can lead to loss of control or accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle vibrates or shakes
the wheel bearing fails
the wheel seizes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or does not start
the key is difficult to turn
the ignition cylinder switch fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to a loss of control, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
the engine RPM drops
the accelerator pedal feels unresponsive
the vehicle hesitates or jerks when accelerating
the "wrench" light or "check engine" light illuminates on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electronic throttle control system can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to a loss of control, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
the engine RPM drops
the accelerator pedal feels unresponsive
the vehicle hesitates or jerks when accelerating
the "wrench" light or "check engine" light illuminates on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cruise control system can cause the vehicle to accelerate or decelerate unexpectedly, leading to a loss of control, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates or decelerates unexpectedly
the cruise control system disengages without warning
the "wrench" light or "check engine" light illuminates on the dashboard.
